<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-08-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                        <head>No. 213.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L.
                                    West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-08-19"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 19, 1886</date>.
                                Received August 20.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday informing me of the causes of
                            complaint alleged by the masters of several American fishing vessels
                            against Captain Quigley, of the Canadian cruiser Terror.</p>
                        <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>